## QA Process

### Step 1 — Content check
```bash
cd phase7/d1
extract-text d1p1_output.pptx
```
Verify: all slides present, no placeholder text (XXXX, TODO, [insert]), LOs on slide 2, classif banner on every slide.

### Step 2 — Visual check (via LibreOffice + pdftoppm)
```bash
soffice --headless --convert-to pdf d1p1_output.pptx
rm -f slide-*.jpg
pdftoppm -jpeg -r 150 d1p1_output.pdf slide
ls -1 "$PWD"/slide-*.jpg
```
Then inspect images for: overflow, overlapping elements, missing content, dark-enough overlay on Higgsfield images.

### Step 3 — Anti-pattern check
Before approving any pack:
- [ ] No white/cream/light backgrounds
- [ ] No decorative lines under titles
- [ ] No numeric data in Calibri (must be Courier New)
- [ ] Classification banner on every slide
- [ ] No same layout three times in a row
- [ ] Dark overlay on every Higgsfield image (min 40% opacity)
- [ ] All text fits within its text box (no overflow)
- [ ] Slide count: max 24 per pack

## Numeric Data Rule
All numeric values on slides — ranges (km), altitudes (ft/m), speeds (kts), frequencies (MHz/GHz), counts, percentages — must use `fontFace: FONT.data` (Courier New). No exceptions.

```js
// Correct
slide.addText('4,000,000', { fontFace: FONT.data, fontSize: 96, ... })

// Wrong
slide.addText('4,000,000', { fontFace: FONT.body, fontSize: 96, ... })
```

## Pack Completion Checklist
Before committing a pack as complete:
- [ ] Build script runs without errors: `node d1p1_build.js`
- [ ] PPTX opens in PowerPoint without corruption
- [ ] All Higgsfield prompts written and images generated
- [ ] Visual QA complete (LibreOffice → pdftoppm → image inspect)
- [ ] Content matches pack LOs and slide count ≤ 24
- [ ] Higgsfield prompt file committed alongside build script
- [ ] Output PPTX committed to `phase7/d1/d1p1_output.pptx`
